# Stateful Spec Methodology

This project uses the **Stateful Spec** methodology for AI-assisted development. All project context, conventions, and iteration history live in `.stateful-spec/`.

Upstream methodology and prompts are synced from [franciscotbjr/stateful-spec](https://github.com/franciscotbjr/stateful-spec) (`main`). Vendored copies: **`.stateful-spec/methodology/`**, **`.stateful-spec/templates/`**, **`.stateful-spec/prompts/`**. Cursor rules under **`.cursor/rules/`** are generated from **`.stateful-spec/prompts/operations/*.md`** (plus project-specific footers).

## Entry Points

1. **`.stateful-spec/memory.md`** — Current project state, active work, constraints. **Read this first** at the start of every session.
2. **`.stateful-spec/project-definition.md`** — Technology stack, conventions, quality gates. The source of truth for how to build.
3. **`.stateful-spec/methodology/`** — Full methodology documentation (phases, roles, decision framework).
4. **`.stateful-spec/templates/`** — Specification, project, and implementation templates (from upstream).
5. **`.stateful-spec/history/`** — Iteration tracking files (one per feature/bugfix/refactor).

## Methodology Phases

Every unit of work follows: **Analyze → Plan → Specify → Implement → Verify**

- Phase guides: `.stateful-spec/methodology/phases/01-analyze.md` through `05-verify.md`
- Roles and expectations: `.stateful-spec/methodology/roles.md`
- Decision framework: `.stateful-spec/methodology/decision-framework.md`

## Operation prompts (Cursor)

Invoke with `@` and the rule name (same stem as the file under `.cursor/rules/`):

| Cursor rule | Purpose |
|-------------|---------|
| `@resume-session` | Load context, summarize state, pick up where you left off |
| `@save-session` | Update `memory.md` and iteration files before ending a session |
| `@create-technical-spec` | Analyze a request and produce a specification |
| `@write-tests` | Generate tests per Project Definition |
| `@debug-issue` | Root cause, minimal fix, regression test |
| `@refactor-code` | Refactor with behavioral preservation |
| `@review-changes` | Self-review before commit or PR |
| `@write-commit-message` | Structured commit message |
| `@update-documentation` | README, CHANGELOG, ARCHITECTURE, rustdoc |

Canonical upstream text for each operation lives in **`.stateful-spec/prompts/operations/<name>.md`**.

**Workflow refresh:** To re-sync from upstream later, follow **`.stateful-spec/prompts/initialization/update-project.md`**.

## Rules for All Work

1. All code must follow the conventions in the Project Definition
2. All quality gates must pass before work is considered complete
3. Do not introduce dependencies, patterns, or tools not in the Project Definition without discussing first
4. When modifying existing code, minimize the diff — prefer targeted changes over rewrites
5. Write tests for any code you add or modify
6. Make small, logical commits that leave the codebase in a working state
